  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as engaging in financial transactions to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of funds through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the funds into the legitimate economy\n\nLegal definitions usually require:\n- Intentional concealment of illegal proceeds\n- Knowledge that funds originated from criminal activity\n- Deliberate attempts to make illegal funds appear legitimate\n\nSpecific details and penalties differ by country and legal system.",
